 Car break-ins are at a high in Mbombela. According to Nelspruit Hi-Tech operations manager Callum MacPherson, there are 15 to 30 break-ins per week, “and those are only the ones that people report.” These criminals park next to your car and then smash your window to steal your valuable goods. READ ALSO: Car break-in caught on camera According to MacPherson the thieves initially used a silver Polo when operating. Howver, locals should also now be on the lookout for a white Polo or a silver Etios. MacPherson gave a few hints as to how you can ensure that your valuables do not get stolen: READ ALSO: VIDEO: CIT robbers hit Fidelity vehicle in Mbombela 